// #2394 sibling shape: a block-wrapped array-REPEAT literal
// (`for x in { [<expr>; N] } { ... }`) shares the same synthetic-`Block`
// desugar as the plain array-literal case, so it hits the identical
// double-free hole once wrapped in a user block. See
// for_in_block_wrapped_array_literal.hew for the full mechanism. Asserted
// against the BUILT NATIVE binary so the double free cannot hide behind
// `hew run`'s masking.
fn main() {
    for x in { [7; 3] } {
        println(x);
    }
}
